#  anti_aliasing, what is it?
Adding pixels of an intermediaty color to the intersections of clusters.
It blunts the edges.

{{fil `:~` Documents/vimwiki/figures/screenshot_20240704_092612.png}}

note, the anti-aliasing pixel does not form a [[cluster___20240619_095817|cluster]] in of itself, rather it blends two clusters boudaries.

It is not good to simply trace the outline of a cluster, this is banding, and will make the sprite look blurred not smoothed.

Using a neutraliser

